name: Blick Art Materials
directions: The back corner, left side from the entrance. There is a yellow stripe on the wall you can see when you walk in, the bathrooms are directly under there.
comment: Staff will welcome you when you come in, but are unintrusive. You don't have to purchase anything. If you browse you may be approached to see if you are finding everything ok. There are two, single stall gender neutral bathrooms, which are cleaned daily and open to the public. The store as a whole is mid-sized and generally pretty mellow in terms of traffic. As an art establishment the store both employs and attracts a fair amount of LBGT+ folk and allys.

name: Department of Speech, Language, and Hearing Sciences
directions:
Entering the building from the south puts you on a landing between 1st and 2nd floors. The bathrooms are just to your left. There are a set of bathrooms on each of the 5 floors.

Wheelchair users- enter from the back of the building (north side). The first floor bathrooms are down the hallway as you head south.
comment: The bathrooms are gendered but include stalls. The 1st floor bathroom is common for people not usually in the building to use.

comment: Customer only bathroom but if you talk to the host they will usually let you use it (better to ask, they'll often stop you if you try to sneak by) Unisex washroom with shared sink area but separate, full door stalls with locks. 2 wheelchair accessible stalls (first stall on your right when you enter and another on the back wall) the restaurant itself is only accessible from a ramp at a back door, requires speaking to an employee.
